INSURANCE
Agent Permission Sets

An agent is a partner user who creates, reviews, and revises quotes, and issues and modifies policies for their customers. But an agent doesn't need access to everything in your org.

We've created permission sets that you can assign to agents to give them access only to the information they need to help their customers succeedâ€”and nothing else.

What Can an Agent Do?

An agent can:

* Create and edit opportunities associated with their parent account.
* Create quotes for their customers.
* Edit quotes and create quote versions.
* Issue policies from quotes and modify existing policies.

Types of Agent Permission Sets

We have created eight agent permission sets for you. Each permission set grants a different level of access to a different set of objects and fields, such as:

* Insurance Create/Update Policy Permission Set
* Insurance Create/Update Quote Permission Set
* Insurance View Policy Permission Set
* Insurance View Quote Permission Set
* Insurance Create/Update Census Data Permission Set

Next Steps

Ready to assign Agent permission sets to your users? Learn how to assign permission sets here.
